"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-03-parisolympics-shanieka-ricketts-wins-olympic-silver-triple-jump\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"KINGSTON, Jamaica- Shanieka Ricketts won a\\u00a0 silver medal after she jumped a season's best 14.87m (-0.7m/s) for second in the women's triple jump at the Olympic Games at Stade de France in Paris on Saturday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 188, \"end\": 193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999956001424994, \"rank\": 4.399876903880254e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a brilliant comeback from her fourth placed finish in Tokyo, Japan three years ago,\\u00a0 and added to her two World Championships silver medals from 2019 in Doha, Qatar and 2022 in Eugene, Oregon.\", \"from\": 208, \"to\": 407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 269, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8724781644873681, \"rank\": 0.14609805698834402, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 276, \"end\": 281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.727085427191932, \"rank\": 0.28307166784316323, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 368, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha_Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.7792657824120091, \"rank\": 0.2832592197581583, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha_Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha_Diamond_League\"}, {\"begin\": 374, \"en